AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Raymond McMillon: Defendant who challenges the sufficiency of the evidence on all three of his convictions and argues about delay attributable to certain matters that occurred 'off the record' and had his trial begin after the court denied his motion to dismiss, requested continuances to file pretrial motions, and was subject to a speedy trial act analysis. He is alleged to have conspired to transport aliens within the United States for commercial advantage or private financial gain.
